<document>
	<title>Multilobular biliary cirrhosis of the liver associated with cystic
   fibrosis (mucoviscidosis).</title>

	<author>Cohn-D.</author>

	<source>Med-J-Aust. 1977 Jan 22. 1(4). P 101-4.</source>

	<abstract>A case (including autopsy findings) is reported of multilobular
   biliary cirrhosis with a strictly nodular liver developing in a 20-
   year-old male with cystic fibrosis (mucoviscidosis). The pathogenesis
   of biliary cirrhosis in cystic fibrosis is briefly discussed.</abstract>

